def: Shifting the sword from one side of an adversary's sword to theother.
A stem structure or stem axis of a plant, viewed as a whole. --Cau*lom"ic (#), a.
Horned; having horns; as, cornigerous animals. [Obs.] Sir T.Browne.
Pertaining to the science or doctrine of refracted sounds.
Denoting a tribe of Franks who established themselves early inthe fourth century on the river Sala [now Yssel]; Salic.-- n.
Of the nature of a provision; serving as a provision for thetime being; -- used of partial or temporary arrangements; as, aprovisional government; a provisional treaty.

The infernal regions, described in the Iliad as situated as farbelow Hades as heaven is above the earth, and by later writers as theplace of punishment for the spirits of the wicked. By the laterpoets, also, the name is often used synonymously with Hades, or theLower World in general.
Having short clauses or sentences; brief; concise.
To cheat defraud grossly, or with deliberate artifice; as, toswindle a man out of his property.Lammote . . . has swindled one of them out of three hundred livres.Carlyle.
Pertaining to fever; indicating fever, or derived from it; as,febrile symptoms; febrile action. Dunglison.
